  <refnamediv>
    <refname>getgaussiankernel</refname>
    <refpurpose>Returns Gaussian filter coefficients</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   output = getgaussiankernel(ksize, sigma, ktype)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>ksize :</term>
      <listitem><para> Aperture size. It should be odd and positive.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>sigma :</term>
      <listitem><para> Gaussian standard deviation.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>ktype :</term>
      <listitem><para> Type of filter coefficients. It can be CV_32f or CV_64F.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The function computes and returns the ksize x 1 matrix of Gaussian filter coefficients.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
output = getgaussiankernel(3,1,'CV_32F');
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

